title: 820-00165 no water damage. No light on MG, no fan spin, all coils 0V
message:
Hi there,

no water damage. No light on MG (1 out of 10 i get orange light that fades out), no fan spin, all coils 0V. Tested with good working io board and cable.
Please advice how to proceed.

Thanks!

title: 820-00165 no water damage. No light on MG, no fan spin, all coils 0V
message:
Post PPBUS_G3H and 3V42_G3H.
If no voltage, post diode mode too.

Keep connected only DC cable, leave out LIO flex.

title: 820-00165 no water damage. No light on MG, no fan spin, all coils 0V
message:
No voltage on both PPBUS_G3H and 3V42_G3H. without LIO flex only with DC cable.
PPBUS_G3H - 137 in diode mode
3V42_G3H - 328 in diode mode

title: 820-00165 no water damage. No light on MG, no fan spin, all coils 0V
message:
Now post PPDCIN_G3H.
If no voltage, post exact R7012 value; measured onboard, ohm scale.
Check if D7012 is not open, or shorted.

title: 820-00165 no water damage. No light on MG, no fan spin, all coils 0V
message:
PPDCIN_G3H at J7000 - jumping between 16.51 - 16.68V
R7012 measured onboard - 56.2k
D7012 - not open. Tested in continuity mode between R7012 pin 2 to R7010 pin 2.
BUT with my sharp eagle eye I saw that pin 2 of D7012 had the smallest oxidation I have ever seen. Replaced it and machine works again.
Thanks for your help!
